# Bluetm Agent kill switch
#
# The autonomous daily upgrade loop in agent/tasks/claude_improvements.py
# checks for a file named `agent/STOP` at the very start of every run.
# If that file exists, the agent exits 0 immediately and does nothing.
#
# Use this when:
#   • You're in the middle of a refactor and don't want the agent running
#     until you've landed your branch.
#   • You suspect the agent has been mis-behaving (drifting, churning,
#     re-proposing rejected ideas) and you want to pause and investigate.
#   • A model upgrade landed and you want to verify behaviour manually
#     before letting the cron fire again.
#
# To halt the agent from anywhere (e.g. your phone via Telegram bridge):
#
#     git checkout -b halt &&
#     touch agent/STOP &&
#     git add agent/STOP &&
#     git commit -m "halt: pause Bluetm Agent" &&
#     git push
#
# Then merge into main when convenient. The next day's cron will see the
# file and exit silently. To re-enable, just delete the file and push.
#
# This file (`agent/STOP.example`) is committed only to document the pattern.
# The real `agent/STOP` is gitignored — drop one locally on rootpc and the
# cron will skip immediately even before the next push.
